message.content: Ranunculus californicus is a flowering plant species native to California, USA. It is also commonly known as California buttercup. The plant is characterized by its showy yellow flowers, with each flower having five petals arranged around a central disk. The flowers are cup-shaped, and can grow up to 3 cm in diameter. The leaves of the plant are lobed, and have a hairy texture. Ranunculus californicus is typically found growing in meadows, grasslands, and woodland habitats. It serves as an important food source for insects such as bees and butterflies.
